{"id":3,"name":"Implement bubble sort algorithm","pattern":"ONE_LIMIT_INCLUSIVE_LOOP--0","patternWeight":[],"constrains":"C1 ONE_LIMIT_INCLUSIVE_LOOP.3-(CTRL)->ONE_LIMIT_INCLUSIVE_LOOP.3|||loop should inside||||||","description":"\nwrite a bubble sort algorithm\n","hint":"bubble sort algorithm using two loops","functionName":"bubbleSort","code":"\n#include <iostream>\nusing namespace std;\n                \nvoid bubbleSort(int arr[], int n){\n    for (int i = 0; i < n-1; i++) {      \n        for (int j = 0; j < n-i-1; j++) { \n            if (arr[j] > arr[j+1]) {\n                int t = arr[j];\n                arr[j] = arr[j + 1];\n                arr[j + 1] = t;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n                 \n// Driver program to test above functions\nint main() {\n    int arr[] = {64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90};\n    int n = sizeof(arr)/sizeof(arr[0]);\n    bubbleSort(arr, n);\n    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {\n        cout << arr[i] << \" \";\n    }\n    return 0;\n}\n"}